## Why This Is Asked

This checks understanding of IND-CCA security and how to build practical, protocol-level defenses in modern cryptographic systems.

## Key Concepts

- IND-CCA and chosen-ciphertext resistance
- Encrypt-then-MAC vs MAC-then-Encrypt
- Nonce management, associated data, and MAC verification order
- Trade-offs: performance, ciphertext size, API surface

## Code Example

```javascript
function encrypt(plaintext, key) {
  const nonce = crypto.randomBytes(12);
  const cipher = crypto.createCipheriv('aes-128-gcm', key, nonce);
  const enc = Buffer.concat([cipher.update(plaintext, 'utf8'), cipher.final()]);
  const tag = cipher.getAuthTag();
  const payload = Buffer.concat([nonce, enc, tag]);
  const mac = crypto.createHmac('sha256', key).update(payload).digest();
  return { payload, mac };
}

function decrypt(payload, mac, key) {
  if (!verifyMac(mac, payload, key)) throw new Error('MAC fail');
  const nonce = payload.slice(0, 12);
  const enc = payload.slice(12, -16);
  const tag = payload.slice(-16);
  const decipher = crypto.createDecipheriv('aes-128-gcm', key, nonce);
  decipher.setAuthTag(tag);
  return Buffer.concat([decipher.update(enc), decipher.final()]);
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you audit for decryption oracle leakage?
- How would you enforce constant-time MAC checks and retry limits to prevent side channels?

## Why This Is Asked
This question probes cross-region consistency, conflict resolution, and practical MongoDB usage.

## Key Concepts
- CAP trade-offs in distributed systems
- Per-field versioning and conflict resolution
- ReadConcern/WriteConcern in MongoDB

## Code Example
```javascript
function mergePrefs(existing, incoming) {
  const out = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(existing || {}));
  for (const key of Object.keys(incoming)) {
    const inc = incoming[key];
    const cur = out[key];
    const tsInc = inc.__version?.ts ?? 0;
    const tsCur = cur?.__version?.ts ?? -1;
    if (tsInc > tsCur || (tsInc === tsCur && (inc.__version?.clientId ?? 0) < (cur?.__version?.clientId ?? 0))) {
      out[key] = inc;
    }
  }
  return out;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test this merge under simultaneous updates?
- How would you adapt for field-level strong consistency needs?
